    <div>
        <p>
            This project demonstrates a simple web application deployed on an AWS EC2 instance as part of a DevOps pipeline. 
            The goal is to show how modern development practices streamline the process of building, testing, and releasing software. 
            By integrating automation and cloud infrastructure, the application becomes easier to maintain and update while ensuring consistent performance across environments.
        </p>

        <p>
            The CI/CD pipeline behind this project handles everything from code integration to automated deployment, 
            reducing manual effort and minimizing the risk of errors. 
            Each change pushed to the repository triggers a sequence of automated steps that validate the code and deliver updates securely to the running application. Security measures such as HTTPS, TLS certificates, and AWS security groups are incorporated to protect the application throughout the development and deployment lifecycle.
        </p>
